      "content": "thanks for the overview. i guess i'm wondering about the \"inclusivity\" part though. i've heard people say that these lessons are basically just \"settled science\" or \"essential for safety\" and that if parents object, they're just being outdated or harmful. is that actually a common way to look at it, or is that just one side talking?",
